Japan's Moves to Grab Tok Islet Condemned 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 21 (KCNA) -- Japan even in its "defence white paper for 2006" absurdly claimed that Tok Islet is part of its territory, a clear indication of its evermore frantic moves to stage a comeback to Korea. This only betrays Japan's brigandish and shameless nature.
 Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No one can vouch that there will be no military clash over Tok Islet, given the Japanese reactionaries' evermore undisguised moves to grab the islet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lurking behind their moves is a sinister intention to provide a military guarantee for the unlimited profits of the Japanese monopoly capital that has grown more inflated than ever before in the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's economy has now swollen to a maximum extent. In order to get rid of this quagmire, Japan is making desperate efforts to put under its control sea lanes for grabbing new areas rich in raw materials and exploring new markets and secure more areas of resources badly needed for it. That is why the Japanese militarists have set their eyes on Tok Islet rich in such resources as natural gas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Tok Islet is also very important from a military point of view. It is the calculation of Japan that its seizure of the islet would make it possible for it to turn vast waters of the East Sea of Korea into its economic waters and zone for the military operation of its "Self-Defence Forces" by exercising the right to 200 mile economic waters. It is in pursuance of this aim that the crafty Japanese militarists deliberately sparked off a territorial dispute, absurdly asserting that the islet is part of their territory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their persistent claim to Tok Islet is also intended to launch the reinvasion of Korea under the pretext of retaking "its land." Their moves to grab the islet are nothing but a prelude to staging a comeback to Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's assertion that the islet is part of its territory can never be justified. The more vociferously Japan advocates its claim to the islet, the more saliently it will reveal its ambition to grab other's land and its wicked scheme to reinvade Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese imperialist war maniacs such as Tojo met miserable ends in the past while frantically waging the war of continental aggression in a bid to realize their "Greater East Asia Co-prosperity Sphere." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries would be well advised to face up to history and the reality and awake from their foolish day dream of grabbing Tok Islet and staging a comeback to Korea.

National Symposium of Pharmacists Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 21 (KCNA) -- A national symposium of pharmacists was held here from Sept. 18 to 20 on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of the start of the institution of "Pharmacopoeia of the DPRK".
 Lectures on the "Pharmacopoeia of the DPRK" were given at the symposium. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They referred to the establishment of certification and quality guarantee system of medical supplies and great achievements made in the field of pharmacology and called on the scientists and technicians in this field to conduct dynamic scientific researches into putting Koryo medicine on an extractive basis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then followed panel discussions on Koryo medicine, pharmaceutics, composition of medicines and foodstuffs for health. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Presented to the symposium were more than 110 papers including the development of TLC-RGB method for the quality control of Koryo medicine and study of the composition of phenazepam. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The symposium was attended by Choe Chang Sik, vice-minister of Public Health who is chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Medical Association, and officials, scientists and technicians in the field of pharmacology.

Meeting of Servicemen and People Held to Complete Kumya River Power Station Earlier than Scheduled 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Kumya, September 20 (KCNA) -- An army-people meeting took place at the construction site of the Kumya River Power Station on Sept. 20 to thoroughly implement the instruction given by Kim Jong Il while providing field guidance to the power station construction site in September of Juche 95 (2006).
 Kim Jong Il clearly indicated the tasks to be undertaken to wind up ahead of schedule the construction of the Kumya River Power Station, a big hydro-power station which is of weighty importance in realizing the nation's electrification, and ways to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter and speakers at the meeting referred to the measures for concentrating all efforts on the project to complete it earlier than scheduled. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called on all the builders of the power station to work a miracle in the construction by displaying popular heroism and total devotion in the efforts to honor the above-said instruction and thus make a tangible contribution to the building of a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If a huge dam is built in the upper reaches of the Kumya River rich in water resources in South Hamgyong Province to form a big man-made lake, this will make it possible to build several power stations in tiers to produce a great deal of electricity, prevent flood damage and sufficiently supply irrigation water to the Kumya Plain.

Scientific and Technological Presentation on Natural Energies Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 21 (KCNA) -- A scientific and technological presentation on natural energies for actively searching and enlisting and effectively using energy resources was held here on Sept. 19 and 20 under the sponsorship of the Central Committee of the Korean General Federation of Science and Technology.
 Over 70 items of research materials and experiences were made public at the presentation which brought together scientists, technicians and working people in the field of thermal power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They included research papers suggesting new solutions to scientific and technological questions arising in developing and utilizing hydro power, solar energy, terrestrial heat, biological gas, etc. such as "Method of Determining Co-ordinates of Wheel Impeller Contours" and "Mock Computer Interpretation of Wheels for Tidal Power Generation".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Presented there were results of scientific and technological researches and experiences for effectively developing and utilizing various energies and saving them and achievements in the research and introduction of different kinds of combustion devices and heat-preserving methods of heating facilities.

Economic and Commercial Councilors' Corps Visits West Sea Barrage 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 21 (KCNA) -- The economic and commercial councilors' corps here visited the West Sea Barrage on Sept. 20 on the occasion of the 58th founding anniversary of the DPRK.
 The guests mounted the observatory to enjoy a bird's-eye view of the barrage, being briefed on it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of their visit Evelio Duenas Ponce, commercial councilor of the Cuban embassy, said it is miracle that the Korean army and people built the barrage in a short span of time, upholding President Kim Il Sung's great plan for remaking nature. The Korean people, rallied close around Kim Jong Il, will surely build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation on this land, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Li Guozhang, first secretary of the Chinese embassy, said that he deeply felt the great vitality of the Korean people's self-reliance whenever he visited the barrage, an edifice of world level, built by the Korean people by their own efforts and technology. He wished them greater success in achieving prosperity of the country and accomplishing the cause of reunification.

Kim Jong Suk and Written Warranty for Good Citizen 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 21 (KCNA) -- The whole life of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk was associated with the ardent love for the people and comrades. The story about a written warranty for a good citizen produced during the anti-Japanese armed struggle is an epitome showing her noble humanities.
 President Kim Il Sung dispatched her to Taoquanli in Changbai County in the northeastern area of China in March Juche 26 (1937), where she conducted underground activities.
 When underground organizations and comrades stood on the brink of exposure, she risked herself to protect them and was arrested by the enemy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The village head who was a member of the underground organization had "friendship" with the chief of the police station. He conducted negotiations with the chief of the police station over her release. The police station chief promised that he would recognize her as a "good citizen" and release her, if the village head prepared a warranty for a good citizen signed by 500 people. He was demanding this document in order to provide documentary evidence for shirking his responsibility, if his superior called the matter into account at a later date. It was common sense that there could not have been such a large number of secret organization members in Taoquanli with only some 200 households. And it was a common, popular mentality not to seal rashly with one's thumb a document testifying that a "disturbing element", spotted as a "traitor" or "communist bandit", was in fact a "good citizen". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But so many villagers placed without hesitation their stamps on the document for her, who regarded herself as not an educator of people but a true servant and daughter of people. They were deeply moved by her human love shown by her for the villagers. She helped them in their household chores. One day a landlord banished his young kitchen maid, suffering from typhoid, into a hut on the mountain. Nobody dared to take care of that pitiable girl. On hearing this news, Kim Jong Suk went to the hut without hesitation and nursed her, sharing bed and meals with her. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the village head prepared such a written warranty and put it on the chief's desk, the chief's eyes almost popped out in astonishment and had no choice but to keep his promise to release her. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The warranty, signed by 500 seals and thumbs, was indeed a miracle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will always remember the devotion and love shown by Kim Jong Suk for the fatherland and the people.

Juche-based Work Method
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 21 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il Sung, who fathered the Juche idea, created and developed in depth the Juche-based work method in the protracted revolutionary struggle for embodying it.
 The method is based on the philosophical principle of the Juche idea that man is the master of everything and decides everything. The essential character of the method lies in the fact that one should always go into people and solve all the problems in reliance upon their strength and wisdom. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President's historical on-the-spot guidance to the Kangson Steel Works(at that time) on December 28, Juche 45(1956) was typical of the embodiment of such method. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The situation of the country was very difficult at that time when it was going to buckle down to the first year task of the vast Five-Year Plan in the teeth of the worsening subversive activities of reactionaries at home and abroad after the Korean war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That day the President called a consultative meeting of leading officials and model workers in the works at which he brought the difficult situation of the country, the requirement of the revolution and the intention of the Party home to workers there and called for producing 10,000 tons of steel more than the plan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 True to his instruction, the working class of the works turned out 120,000 tons of steel with a 60,000-ton-capacity blooming mill shattering all the antiquated ideas such as passivism and mysticism about technology and displaying the revolutionary zeal and creative ingenuity. Their efforts initiated the Chollima work-team movement which swept all over the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President, with the Juche-based work method, closely rallied the popular masses around the Party and gave rise to their revolutionary enthusiasm and creative ingenuity at each period and each stage of the revolutionary development, thus dynamically propelling the revolution and construction.
